<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFDEFFD2FF75FEDF15B9C23F" blockId="9.[189,754,337,359]" box="[189,754,337,359]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<heading id="D08281EBFFDEFFD2FF75FEDF15B9C23F" box="[189,754,337,359]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFDEFFD2FF75FEDF15B9C23F" authority="(TOWNSEND, 1898)" baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[189,754,337,359]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamaulipanum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFDEFFD2FF75FEDF1545C23D" box="[189,526,337,358]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">COPESTYLUM TAMAULIPANUM</emphasis>
(TOWNSEND, 1898)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFDEFFD2FF6CFEF615C1C13B" blockId="9.[164,779,375,611]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFDEFFD2FF6CFEF616E7C2D5" box="[164,428,375,397]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">Larva and puparium:</emphasis>
Anterior fold without extra large spicules. Anterior spiracles with three openings. Abdominal vestiture of short, upright setae. Anal lobe without spicules. Posterior breathing tube orange, tapering. AP smooth, shiny and as long as TR is wide. Pupal spiracles orange, matt, and with three encircling rings of openings in upper third. Pupal spiracles as wide apart as a pupal spiracle is long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36F650CFFDEFFD2FF6CFD001687C7EA" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFDEFFD2FF6CFD0017AAC003" blockId="9.[164,779,654,859]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFDEFFD2FF6CFD0015E4C1FB" box="[164,687,654,675]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
Taxonomic notes: 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFDEFFD2FEBDFD0015E4C1FB" baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[373,687,654,675]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamaulipanum">Copestylum tamaulipanum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFDEFFD2FEE1FD2316F0C199" box="[297,443,684,706]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alberlena">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFDEFFD2FEE1FD2316F0C199" box="[297,443,684,706]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">C. alberlena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFDEFFD2FDCCFD2315AFC199" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[516,740,684,706]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multipunctatum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFDEFFD2FDCCFD2315AFC199" box="[516,740,684,706]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">C. multipunctatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a tapering posterior breathing tube and light orange pupal spiracles. It differs from both these species in the AP that is as long as the TR is wide. In the latter two species the AP is shorter than the TR is wide.
</paragraph>
